1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact subsections 1, 17, and 18 of section 12.1-34-02 of the
2 North Dakota Century Code, relating to fair treatment of victims.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsections 1, 17, and 18 of section 12.1-34-02 of the North
5 Dakota Century Code are amended and reenacted as follows:
6 1. Informed by those entities that have contact with the victim or witness when requested
7 as to the availability of and the methods available for registration with the statewide
8 automated victim information and notification system. Those entities include law
9 enforcement, prosecuting attorneys, the courts, and custodial authorities. A victim or
10 witness who clearly objects to registration may not be required to register with the
11 system or must be able to opt out of the system. A victim has the right to:
12 a. Prevent the disclosure of confidential or privileged information about the victim or
13 the victim's family; and
14 b. Be notified of any request for identifying information or confidential or privileged
15 information about the victim or victim's family.
16 17. Prompt notice of custodial release. Registered victims and witnesses must be
17 informed whenever a criminal defendant receives a temporary, provisional, or final
18 release from custody or whenever the defendant escapes from custody. Victims who
19 are not registered must be given the same notice by the appropriate custodial
20 authority. Notification must include the transfer of the defendant to a work-release or
21 education release program, a community residential program, or transfer to a mental
22 health facility. All notices to the registered victim and witnesses concerning this release
23 information must be within a reasonable time prior to the defendant's release or
